Name: The Stone Foxes
rawData:
The Stone Foxes is an American rock and roll band based in San Francisco, California, United States.
The Stone Foxes originated in the sleepy foothills of California’s Central Valley where founding members Aaron Mort and brothers Spence Koehler (guitar) and Shannon Koehler (drums, vocals) grew up. After high school, they went to college at San Francisco State University.
A couple of years later, after living with the three founding members and discovering their similar musical tastes, Avi Vinocur (guitar, bass) joined the band.

Genres: Blues rock, hard rock, soul, rock and roll
Associated acts: The Black Keys, Cage the Elephant
